					<msContents>
						<summary>

						<p>Stone (No. 2) lying in the compound of the local court.</p>						

						<p>1748 A.D.</p>						

						<p>This is dated <hi rend="bold">Śaka 1670, Vibhva, [Vaiśākha] śu. 10, Sunday.</hi> These details are irregular as the <hi rend="italic">tithi</hi> corresponds to <hi rend="bold">1748 A.D., April 27</hi> when the weekday was Wednesday.</p>						

						<p>It states that the village Sāṇḍūru was given as <hi rend="italic">Vumiḷigi</hi> to Jamunāgiri-svāmi and that the latters <hi rend="italic">samādhi</hi> was built by Giriyamma. The record is written both in Kannaḍa and Telugu languages.</p>						

						</summary>
					</msContents>
